UNITED STATES, Plaintiff-Appellee, v. CHEW MOO, Defendant-Appellant. UNITED STATES, Plaintiff-Appellee, v. YEE MOOK, Defendant-Appellant. No. 379. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. March 20, 1934. James C. Thomas, of New York City, for appellants. Martin Conboy, U. S. Atty., of New York City (Bronson Goddard, Asst. U. S. Atty., of New York City, of counsel), for the United States.

Before L. HAND, SWAN, and AUGUSTUS N. HAND, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Affirmed in open court.
